commit.message: build: Fix undefined X11 references.

extras/immodules/client-qt: build with Qt5.

  - Remove Qt3 and Qt4 codes.

  - This version of Qt5 builds and loads successfully, but cannot be
    actived and input characters.

  - Adoption to Qt5:

    1. Replace all #ifdef QT4 blocks to unconditional counterparts.
    2. Remove all #ifdef Q_WS_X11 blocks, as is not supported by Qt5.
    3. Migrated QInputContextPlugin -> QPlatformInputContextPlugin.

extras/immodules/client-qt: Start porting to Qt5.

  Adopt qmake for fast iteration of Qt5 plugin alone.

configure.ac Makefile.am: patch out Qt clients.

  The existing modules does not support Qt5, and GNU/Linux
  distributions like Debian are migrating to Qt5-only repositories.

Bug: https://bugs.debian.org/851827
